<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="120" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,903,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1047,1072]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName box="[695,880,1047,1072]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salicis">
<emphasis box="[695,880,1047,1072]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">Stigmella salicis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (for the world catalogue of this group see Puplesis &amp; Diškus, 
<number box="[371,432,1084,1108]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" value="2003.0">2003</number>
). In male genitalia, it differs from all other species of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1070,1141,1084,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salicis">
<emphasis box="[1070,1141,1084,1109]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">salicis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by the combination of very large cornuti aggregated in two lateral rows and the large medial plate of gnathos; the host-plant (
<taxonomicName box="[160,408,1156,1181]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Podanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ovatifolius">
<emphasis box="[160,408,1156,1181]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">Podanthus ovatifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) also makes this species distinctive. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName box="[993,1225,1156,1181]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="podanthae">
<emphasis box="[993,1225,1156,1181]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">Stigmella podanthae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from most similar but Rosaceae-feeding Ecuadorian 
<taxonomicName box="[638,849,1192,1216]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanotropica">
<emphasis box="[638,849,1192,1216]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">S. montanotropica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the forewing fascia (in 
<taxonomicName box="[1179,1390,1192,1216]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanotropica">
<emphasis box="[1179,1390,1192,1216]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">S. montanotropica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the forewing is uniformly coloured, without fascia), and by 
<number box="[805,832,1228,1252]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" value="11.0">11</number>
cornuti (instead 
<quantity box="[1031,1091,1228,1253]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.556" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" unit="in" value="14.0">14 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName box="[1100,1310,1229,1252]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanotropica">
<emphasis box="[1100,1310,1229,1252]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">S. montanotropica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); from the superficially similar Colombian 
<taxonomicName authority="Zeller" authorityName="Zeller" box="[517,737,1263,1288]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="johannis">
<emphasis box="[517,642,1263,1288]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">S. johannis</emphasis>
(Zeller)
</taxonomicName>
by the larger lateral lobes of vinculum, larger medial plate of gnathos, uncus divided in two large lobes (not into equally small four ones as in 
<taxonomicName box="[1091,1218,1300,1325]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="johannis">
<emphasis box="[1091,1218,1300,1325]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">S. johannis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and by the small transtilla with short sublateral processes (in 
<taxonomicName box="[640,765,1335,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="johannis">
<emphasis box="[640,765,1335,1360]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">S. johannis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
transtilla is rounded, without processes, and extending from the ventral plate of vinculum).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="121" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,903,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1407,1432]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[276,361,1407,1432]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 17" captionStartId="7.[151,264,970,993]" captionTargetBox="[172,1418,193,935]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[153,1433,193,949]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 17. Adults. 14, 15, male (14) and female (15) of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov.; 16, 17, male (16) and female (17) of Astrotischeria chilei Puplesis &amp; Diškus. Note: the forewing pattern is highly variable, the pattern (17, female) when ochreyellow scales predominate and black scales form irregular dots is equally characteristic for males." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268269/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">
Fig. 
<number box="[330,361,1408,1432]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). Forewing length 2.2–2.6 mm; wingspan 4.3–5.5 mm. Head: palpi greyish cream; frontal tuft yellowish cream to beige cream or very pale orange; collar and scape very large, yellowish cream; antenna with 
<number box="[1408,1436,1444,1468]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" value="30.0">30</number>
segments, distinctly longer than half of forewing; flagellum dark grey or fuscous on upper side, grey to cream grey on underside. Thorax, tegulae and forewing very densely irrorated with brown-black or black scales with purple iridescence. Forewing with distinctly postmedian, slightly oblique or straight, greyish cream or whitish fascia strongly narrowed or fully interrupted in the middle; cilia pale grey to dark grey, with overlapping apical spot of lamellar whitish cream scales; underside of forewing black-grey, without spots. Hindwing and its cilia grey to pale grey; underside of hindwing grey to fuscous grey. Legs pale grey to fuscous on upper side, yellowish cream or beige on underside. Abdomen fuscous on upper side, cream beige to grey yellow on underside; anal tufts short, beige; anal plates cream beige.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,903,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1767,1792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[305,393,1767,1792]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 17" captionStartId="7.[151,264,970,993]" captionTargetBox="[172,1418,193,935]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[153,1433,193,949]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 17. Adults. 14, 15, male (14) and female (15) of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov.; 16, 17, male (16) and female (17) of Astrotischeria chilei Puplesis &amp; Diškus. Note: the forewing pattern is highly variable, the pattern (17, female) when ochreyellow scales predominate and black scales form irregular dots is equally characteristic for males." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268269/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">
Fig. 
<number box="[362,393,1767,1792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
). Externally similar to male but forewing fascia 
<number box="[967,980,1767,1792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" value="2.0">2</number>
–2.5 times broader, cream to yellowish cream, and not narrowed (constricted or interrupted) in the middle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,903,2009]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,861]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="121" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,370,1839,1864]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[385,518,1839,1864]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1728,1751]" captionTargetBox="[201,1413,203,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1433,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 24. Male genitalia of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. (ZMUC). 18, capsule (without phallus), holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 19, phallus, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 20, same, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 591; 21, uncus and gnathos, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 593; 22, cornuti, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 23, apical parts of valvae, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 24, dorsal view of genital capsule, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 591." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268270/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">
Figs 
<number box="[443,518,1840,1864]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" value="21.0" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="18.0">18–24</number>
</figureCitation>
). Capsule 
<number box="[635,733,1840,1864]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" value="295.0" valueMax="300.0" valueMin="290.0">290–300</number>
Μm long. Vinculum with short triangular lateral lobes; ventral plate small (
<number box="[287,317,1876,1900]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" value="40.0">40</number>
Μm long in the middle). Uncus gradually narrowed caudally, divided in two large lobes each bearing two papillae (
<figureCitation box="[304,478,1911,1936]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1728,1751]" captionTargetBox="[201,1413,203,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1433,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 24. Male genitalia of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. (ZMUC). 18, capsule (without phallus), holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 19, phallus, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 20, same, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 591; 21, uncus and gnathos, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 593; 22, cornuti, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 23, apical parts of valvae, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 24, dorsal view of genital capsule, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 591." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268270/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">
Figs 
<number box="[361,434,1912,1936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" value="18.21">18, 21</number>
, 
<number box="[446,478,1912,1936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
). Gnathos with large central plate and two parallel and very slender caudal processes (
<figureCitation box="[159,246,1948,1973]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1728,1751]" captionTargetBox="[201,1413,203,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1433,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 24. Male genitalia of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. (ZMUC). 18, capsule (without phallus), holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 19, phallus, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 20, same, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 591; 21, uncus and gnathos, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 593; 22, cornuti, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 23, apical parts of valvae, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 24, dorsal view of genital capsule, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 591." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268270/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">
Fig. 
<number box="[215,246,1948,1972]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
). Valva (
<figureCitation box="[353,488,1948,1973]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1728,1751]" captionTargetBox="[201,1413,203,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1433,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 24. Male genitalia of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. (ZMUC). 18, capsule (without phallus), holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 19, phallus, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 20, same, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 591; 21, uncus and gnathos, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 593; 22, cornuti, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 23, apical parts of valvae, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 24, dorsal view of genital capsule, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 591." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268270/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">
Figs 
<number box="[414,488,1948,1972]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" value="18.23">18, 23</number>
</figureCitation>
) 
<number box="[507,549,1948,1973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" value="165.0">165</number>
Μm long, small inner lobe, inwardly-bent apex with two pointed processes; transtilla with short, slightly variable sublateral processes (
<figureCitation box="[837,975,1984,2009]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1728,1751]" captionTargetBox="[201,1413,203,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1433,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 24. Male genitalia of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. (ZMUC). 18, capsule (without phallus), holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 19, phallus, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 20, same, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 591; 21, uncus and gnathos, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 593; 22, cornuti, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 23, apical parts of valvae, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 24, dorsal view of genital capsule, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 591." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268270/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="120">
Figs 
<number box="[897,975,1984,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" value="18.24">18, 24</number>
</figureCitation>
). Juxta membranous, indistinct. Phallus (
<figureCitation box="[159,328,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1728,1751]" captionTargetBox="[201,1413,203,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1433,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 24. Male genitalia of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. (ZMUC). 18, capsule (without phallus), holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 19, phallus, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 20, same, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 591; 21, uncus and gnathos, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 593; 22, cornuti, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 23, apical parts of valvae, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 24, dorsal view of genital capsule, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 591." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268270/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">
Figs 
<number box="[215,288,152,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="19.2">19, 20</number>
, 
<number box="[299,328,152,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
) 
<number box="[343,441,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="207.5" valueMax="225.0" valueMin="190.0">190–225</number>
Μm long, 
<number box="[555,625,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="77.5" valueMax="80.0" valueMin="75.0">75–80</number>
Μm broad; vesica with 
<number box="[887,914,152,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="11.0">11</number>
various spine-like cornuti aggregated into two lateral clusters (
<figureCitation box="[329,413,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1728,1751]" captionTargetBox="[201,1413,203,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[153,1433,193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 24. Male genitalia of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. (ZMUC). 18, capsule (without phallus), holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 19, phallus, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 20, same, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 591; 21, uncus and gnathos, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 593; 22, cornuti, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 23, apical parts of valvae, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 592; 24, dorsal view of genital capsule, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD 591." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268270/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">
Fig. 
<number box="[381,413,188,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,404,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(Figs 
<number box="[492,567,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="27.0" valueMax="29.0" valueMin="25.0">25–29</number>
). Total length 
<number box="[752,794,224,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="710.0">710</number>
Μm. Abdominal apex distinctly truncate. Apophyses anteriores (
<quantity box="[283,363,260,285]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" unit="m" value="125.0">125 m</quantity>
) almost equal to very narrow apophyses posteriores (
<number box="[1014,1057,260,284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="130.0">130</number>
Μm) (Figs 
<number box="[1202,1282,260,284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="27.28">27, 28</number>
). Vestibulum relatively narrow, without sclerites. Accessory sac large and folded. Ductus spermathecae narrow and long, with one small but strongly chitinized convolution (Fig. 
<number box="[753,784,332,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="25.0">25</number>
); extending into oval utriculus (Fig. 
<number box="[1216,1248,332,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="26.0">26</number>
). Corpus bursae round (
<number box="[231,275,367,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="350.0">350</number>
Μm long, 
<number box="[389,431,367,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="295.0">295</number>
Μm broad), covered with numerous irregular granules but without signa (Figs 
<number box="[1310,1384,367,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="25.26">25, 26</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,330,404,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">Bionomics.</emphasis>
Mines in leaves (
<figureCitation box="[559,669,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1769,1792]" captionTargetBox="[181,1409,231,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[153,1433,231,1745]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Geography and biology of the treated leaf-mining species. 1, distribution of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. and Astrotischeria chilei Puplesis &amp; Diškus; 2, central Mediterranean Chile at elevation about 910 m (18 km southeast of Pirque, Rio Clarillo); 3, Host-plant Podanthus ovatifolius Lag.; 4, same, with a leaf-mine of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov.; 5, 6, leafmines of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. Podanthus ovatifolius Lag., 18 km southeast of Pirque, Rio Clarillo." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268268/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">
Figs 
<number box="[623,669,404,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Host-plant: 
<taxonomicName authority="Lag." authorityName="Lag." box="[836,1156,404,429]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Podanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ovatifolius">
<emphasis box="[836,1089,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">Podanthus ovatifolius</emphasis>
Lag.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1177,1306,404,428]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
: subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[151,284,439,464]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Asteroideae">
<emphasis box="[151,284,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">Asteroideae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: tribe 
<taxonomicName box="[361,498,439,464]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Heliantheae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[361,498,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">Heliantheae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[524,629,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1769,1792]" captionTargetBox="[181,1409,231,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[153,1433,231,1745]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Geography and biology of the treated leaf-mining species. 1, distribution of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. and Astrotischeria chilei Puplesis &amp; Diškus; 2, central Mediterranean Chile at elevation about 910 m (18 km southeast of Pirque, Rio Clarillo); 3, Host-plant Podanthus ovatifolius Lag.; 4, same, with a leaf-mine of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov.; 5, 6, leafmines of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. Podanthus ovatifolius Lag., 18 km southeast of Pirque, Rio Clarillo." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268268/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">
Figs 
<number box="[582,629,440,464]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="3.4">3, 4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Egg on upper side of the leaf. Larvae mine in April (start feeding in early April). Sinuous or contorted gallery of mine with black frass; early mine (first third or half of mine) very slender and completely or almost completely filled with frass (
<figureCitation box="[875,945,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1769,1792]" captionTargetBox="[181,1409,231,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[153,1433,231,1745]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Geography and biology of the treated leaf-mining species. 1, distribution of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. and Astrotischeria chilei Puplesis &amp; Diškus; 2, central Mediterranean Chile at elevation about 910 m (18 km southeast of Pirque, Rio Clarillo); 3, Host-plant Podanthus ovatifolius Lag.; 4, same, with a leaf-mine of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov.; 5, 6, leafmines of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. Podanthus ovatifolius Lag., 18 km southeast of Pirque, Rio Clarillo." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268268/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">
Fig. 
<number box="[929,945,511,536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
); the remaining two-thirds or half of mine almost abruptly become broad, with disperse or coiled frass deposited in an irregular, broad central line occupying one-third of the width of the gallery (
<figureCitation box="[568,670,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1769,1792]" captionTargetBox="[181,1409,231,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[153,1433,231,1745]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Geography and biology of the treated leaf-mining species. 1, distribution of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. and Astrotischeria chilei Puplesis &amp; Diškus; 2, central Mediterranean Chile at elevation about 910 m (18 km southeast of Pirque, Rio Clarillo); 3, Host-plant Podanthus ovatifolius Lag.; 4, same, with a leaf-mine of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov.; 5, 6, leafmines of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. Podanthus ovatifolius Lag., 18 km southeast of Pirque, Rio Clarillo." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268268/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">
Figs 
<number box="[625,670,583,608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="5.6">5, 6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Larva green (or yellowish green), with beige-brown intestine (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1769,1792]" captionTargetBox="[181,1409,231,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[153,1433,231,1745]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Geography and biology of the treated leaf-mining species. 1, distribution of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. and Astrotischeria chilei Puplesis &amp; Diškus; 2, central Mediterranean Chile at elevation about 910 m (18 km southeast of Pirque, Rio Clarillo); 3, Host-plant Podanthus ovatifolius Lag.; 4, same, with a leaf-mine of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov.; 5, 6, leafmines of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. Podanthus ovatifolius Lag., 18 km southeast of Pirque, Rio Clarillo." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268268/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,167,620,645]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
); in final instar predominantly yellowish, with beige-brown intestine (
<figureCitation box="[954,1022,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1769,1792]" captionTargetBox="[181,1409,231,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[153,1433,231,1745]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Geography and biology of the treated leaf-mining species. 1, distribution of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. and Astrotischeria chilei Puplesis &amp; Diškus; 2, central Mediterranean Chile at elevation about 910 m (18 km southeast of Pirque, Rio Clarillo); 3, Host-plant Podanthus ovatifolius Lag.; 4, same, with a leaf-mine of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov.; 5, 6, leafmines of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. Podanthus ovatifolius Lag., 18 km southeast of Pirque, Rio Clarillo." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268268/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">
Fig. 
<number box="[1006,1022,620,645]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Larval exit slit on upper side of the leaf. Cocoon pale beige; length 2.1–2.2 mm, maximal width 1.2 mm. Adult emergence in May.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">
Using the ‘Formula of Evaluation of Abundance and Occurrence of Leaf-miners’ (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Diskus" box="[1130,1382,692,717]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="123" pageId="2" pageNumber="122" refString="Diskus, A. &amp; Stonis, J. R. (2012) Leaf-mining insects of Lithuania. The Nepticulidae (Lepidoptera): taxonomy, chorological composition and trophic relationships. Monograph [in Lithuanian]. Lutute Publishers, Kaunas, 220 pp." type="book" year="2012">
Diškus &amp; Stonis 
<number box="[1322,1382,692,716]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="2012.0">2012</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="53.0" valueMax="54.0" valueMin="52.0">52– 54</number>
), it appears that 
<taxonomicName box="[370,517,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="podanthae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[370,517,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">S. podanthae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[525,615,727,752]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[525,615,727,752]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is not rare at the 
<typeStatus box="[815,863,728,752]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<quantity box="[972,1044,727,752]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" unit="km" value="18.0">18 km</quantity>
southeast of Pirque) (Rio Clarillo, figs 
<number box="[200,245,764,788]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="1.2">1, 2</number>
): It is limited in distribution but abundant (more than 
<number box="[848,876,764,788]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="20.0">20</number>
leaf-mines recorded at a single site).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1385,799,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,861]" box="[199,1385,799,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,799,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[360,461,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1769,1792]" captionTargetBox="[181,1409,231,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[153,1433,231,1745]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Geography and biology of the treated leaf-mining species. 1, distribution of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. and Astrotischeria chilei Puplesis &amp; Diškus; 2, central Mediterranean Chile at elevation about 910 m (18 km southeast of Pirque, Rio Clarillo); 3, Host-plant Podanthus ovatifolius Lag.; 4, same, with a leaf-mine of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov.; 5, 6, leafmines of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. Podanthus ovatifolius Lag., 18 km southeast of Pirque, Rio Clarillo." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268268/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">
Figs 
<number box="[417,461,800,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="1.2">1, 2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Known only from central Mediterranean 
<collectingCountry box="[943,1003,799,824]" name="Chile" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">Chile</collectingCountry>
at elevation about 
<quantity box="[1217,1287,800,824]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.1" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" unit="m" value="910.0">910 m</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[1303,1371,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1769,1792]" captionTargetBox="[181,1409,231,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[153,1433,231,1745]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Geography and biology of the treated leaf-mining species. 1, distribution of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. and Astrotischeria chilei Puplesis &amp; Diškus; 2, central Mediterranean Chile at elevation about 910 m (18 km southeast of Pirque, Rio Clarillo); 3, Host-plant Podanthus ovatifolius Lag.; 4, same, with a leaf-mine of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov.; 5, 6, leafmines of Stigmella podanthae sp. nov. Podanthus ovatifolius Lag., 18 km southeast of Pirque, Rio Clarillo." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268268/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="121">
Fig. 
<number box="[1355,1371,800,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="121" value="2.0">2</number>
